data.name: _slNote.Text
data.value:
Hide

Note on DataSource.Filter syntax:

Syntax used by the DataSource.Filter expression differs from regular VBScript used in other C1Report expressions and scripts. It is the same syntax that is used to specify the System.Data.DataView.RowFilter property for System.Data.DataView objects. For a detailed description of the syntax see DataColumn.Expression. For details on using DataSource.Filter see C1Report online help.

Auto Syntax Check is not available when editing filter expressions. Syntax Highlighting works and uses the proper syntax.

data.name: rbtnOK.ToolTip
data.value:
Done (Ctrl+W)

Close the VBScript Editor window.

Any unsaved changes will be automatically saved.

(To exit the VBScript Eitor without saving the current script, press the X button in the top right corner of the editor window.)

data.name: rbtnPaste.ToolTip
data.value:
Paste (Ctrl+V)
Insert content on the Clipboard into the document.

data.name: rbtnCut.ToolTip
data.value:
Cut (Ctrl+X)
Remove selection from the document and put it on the Clipboard.

data.name: rbtnCopy.ToolTip
data.value:
Copy (Ctrl+C)
Put a copy of the selection on the Clipboard.

data.name: rbtnDelete.ToolTip
data.value:
Delete (Del)
Delete the current selection.

data.name: rbtnUndo.ToolTip
data.value: Undo (Ctrl+Z)

data.name: rbtnRedo.ToolTip
data.value: Redo (Ctrl+Y)

data.name: rmnuDataFields.ToolTip
data.value:
Database Fields

Insert a database field's name. The name evaluates to the current field value when the script executes.

Note that the database fields can also be inserted via the C1Report | Database Fields context menu.

data.name: rmnuReportFields.ToolTip
data.value:
Report Fields

Insert a report field's name. The name evaluates to the current field value when the script executes.

Note that the report fields can also be inserted via the C1Report | Report Fields context menu.

data.name: rmnuReportGlobals.ToolTip
data.value:
Global Scripts

Insert the name of a Function or a Sub defined in the GlobalScripts property. The specified function or sub will be called when the script executes.

Note that the globals can also be inserted via the C1Report | Global Scripts context menu.

data.name: rmnuReportMore.ToolTip
data.value:
More

Insert the name of a report section, a report script variable or a report aggregate function.

Note that report section names, script varialbles and aggregate functions can also be inserted via the C1Report | More context menu.

data.name: rmnuVBScriptFunctions.ToolTip
data.value:
Functions

Insert the name of a standard VBScript function.

Note that the standard VBScript functions can can also be inserted via the VBScript | Functions context menu.

data.name: rmnuVBScriptProgram.ToolTip
data.value:
Program

Insert a VBScript keyword, constant, conditional statement or function/sub construct.

Note that the same VBScript constructs can can also be inserted via the VBScript | Program context menu.

data.name: rbEditorFontName.ToolTip
data.value:
Font
Pick a font to use in the VBScript Editor.

data.name: rbFontSize.ToolTip
data.value:
Size
Select the font size.

data.name: rbtnFontSizeUp.ToolTip
data.value:
Increase Font Size
Increase the font size by 1pt.

data.name: rbtnFontSizeDown.ToolTip
data.value:
Decrease Font Size
Decrease the font size by 1pt.

data.name: rbTextColor.ToolTip
data.value:
Text Color

Select the default text color for the VBScript Editor.

Note that Syntax Highlighting overrides the text color of many syntax elements.

data.name: rbBackgroundColor.ToolTip
data.value:
Background
Select the background color for the VBScript Editor.

data.name: rbSyntaxHighlight.ToolTip
data.value:
Syntax Highlighting
Turn syntax highlighting on or off.

data.name: rbSyntaxAutoCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Auto Syntax Check

Turn automatic syntax checking on or off.

If this option is on, and the current script contains errors, the first error will be shown in the status bar.

data.name: rbDataSourceFilterWarning.ToolTip
data.value:
DataSource.Filter Warning

Display a note about DataSource.Filter syntax when editing a filter expression.

Unlike other expressions and scripts in C1Report which use VBScript, the DataSource.Filter expression uses a special expression syntax like that used in System.Data.DataColumn.Expression. If this option is on, a warning note appears in the bottom part of the editor window when editing a filter expression.

data.name: rbAutoSave.ToolTip
data.value:
Autosave Current Script

Turn automatic saving of the current script on or off.

If this option is on, and the current script in the editor has changed, switching to another script will automatically save the changes.

If this option is off, a dialog will show asking whether to save the changes.
